|mi|abbr=on}} || [[File:Mountainstage.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] || Stage with mountain(s) || {{flagathlete|[[Joseph van Dam]]|BEL}} || {{flagathlete|[[Lucien Buysse]]|BEL}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1926 Tour de France, Stage 10 to Stage 17#Stage 16|16]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 17 July|| [[Evian]] to [[Dijon]] ||{{convert|321|km|mi|abbr=on}} || [[File:Plainstage.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] || Plain stage || {{flagathlete|[[Camille van de Casteele]]|BEL}} || {{flagathlete|[[Lucien Buysse]]|BEL}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1926 Tour de France, Stage 10 to Stage 17#Stage 17|17]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 18 July|| [[Dijon]] to [[Paris]] ||{{convert|341|km|mi|abbr=on}} || [[File:Plainstage.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] || Plain stage || {{flagathlete|[[Aim\u00e9 Dossche]]|BEL}} || {{flagathlete|[[Lucien Buysse]]|BEL}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"| Total\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center\"| {{convert|5745|km|0|abbr=on}}{{sfn|Augendre|2016|p=108}}\n|}\n\n===General classification===\n[[File:Lucien Buysse in de Tour de France 1926.jpg|thumb|right|[[Lucien Buysse]], the winner of the 1926 Tour de France.]]\nThe race was won by Belgian Lucien Buysse.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:42em;margin-bottom:0;\"\n|+ Final general classification (1\u201310)<ref name=\"mdc1926\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Rank!! scope=\"col\" | Rider!! scope=\"col\" | Sponsor!! scope=\"col\" | Time\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |1\n| {{flagathlete|[[Lucien Buysse]]|BEL}} || Automoto\u2013Hutchinson || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 238h 44' 25\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |2\n| {{flagathlete|[[Nicolas Frantz]]|LUX}} || Alcyon\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+1h 22' 25\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |3\n| {{flagathlete|[[Bartolomeo Aimo]]|ITA|1861}} || Alcyon\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+1h 22' 51\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |4\n| {{flagathlete|[[Th\u00e9ophile Beeckman]]|BEL}} || Armor\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+1h 43' 54\"\n|-\n! scop