]]|BEL}} || Alcyon\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+6h 03' 10\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |18\n| {{flagathlete|[[Henri Colle]]|BEL}} || Jean Louvet \u2013 Hutchinson || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+7h 10' 35\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |19\n| {{flagathlete|[[Georges Detreille]]|FRA}} || Meteore\u2013Wolber || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+7h 48' 17\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |20\n| {{flagathlete|[[Omer Vermeulen]]|BEL}} || Meteore\u2013Wolber || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+7h 49' 44\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |21\n| {{flagathlete|[[Giovanni Rossignoli]]|ITA|1861}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+8h 23' 29\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |22\n| {{flagathlete|[[Alfons Standaert]]|BEL}} || Armor\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+9h 37' 02\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |23\n| {{flagathlete|[[Benoit Faure]]|FRA}} || Meteore\u2013Wolber || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+9h 35' 44\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |24\n| {{flagathlete|[[Henri Touzard]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+9h 36' 34\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |25\n| {{flagathlete|[[L\u00e9on Devos (cyclist)|L\u00e9on Devos]]|BEL}} || Thomann\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+10h 05' 23\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |26\n| {{flagathlete|[[Jan Mertens (cyclist)|Jan Mertens]]|BEL}} || Labor\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+10h 27' 05\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |27\n| {{flagathlete|[[Paul Duboc]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+10h 30' 47\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |28\n| {{flagathlete|[[Louis Delannoy]]|BEL}} || Labor\u2013Dunlop || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+10h 41' 09\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |29\n| {{flagathlete|[[Eug\u00e8ne Dhers]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+11h 26' 16\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |30\n| {{flagathlete|[[Carlo Longoni]]|ITA|1861}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+11h 50' 56\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |31\n| {{flagathlete|[[Charles Martinet (cyclist)|Charles Martinet]]|SUI}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+12h 56' 13\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |32\n| {{flagathlete|[[Fernand Saive]]|BEL}} || Meteore\u2013Wolber || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+13h 59' 59\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |33\n| {{flagathlete|[[Maurice Arnoult]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+14h 24' 52\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |34\n| {{flagathlete|[[Henri Catelan]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+15h 53' 32\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |35\n| {{flagathlete|[[Mose Arrosio]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+17h 12' 30\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |36\n| {{flagathlete|[[Fernand Moulet]]|FRA}} || Meteore\u2013Wolber || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+18h 00' 43\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |37\n| {{flagathlete|[[Alfred Francini]]|ITA|1861}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+18h 18' 25\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |38\n| {{flagathlete|[[Edouard Teisseire]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+19h 14' 17\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |39\n| {{flagathlete|[[Henri Ferrara]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+21h 00' 22\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |40\n| {{flagathlete|[[Jules Gillard]]|SUI}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+22h 47' 44\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |41\n| {{flagathlete|[[Andr\u00e9 Drobecq]]|FRA}} || \u2014 || style=\"text-align:right;\" |+24h 59' 03\"\n|}\n\n==Other classifications==\nThe race for ''touriste-routiers'', cyclists who did not belong to a team and were allowed no assistance, was won by Italian Rossignoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.letour.fr/HISTO/fr/TDF/1926/histoire.html|title=l'Historique du Tour - Ann\u00e9e 1926|language=French|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|accessdate=15 January 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100709024743/http://www.letour.fr/HISTO/fr/TDF/1926/histoire.html|archive-date=9 July 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe organising newspaper, [[l'Auto]] named a ''meilleur grimpeur'' (best climber), an unofficial precursor to the modern [[King of the Mountains]] competition. This award was won by Lucien Buysse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tour-giro-vuelta.net|title=Tour-giro-vuelta|accessdate=21 September 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nLucien Buysse announced after his win that he expected to win again in 1927, but because his sponsor Automoto had financial problems, they could not send a team to the Tours of 1927 and 1928, and Buysse only returned in 1929.<ref name=\"trouw\"/> Lucien Buysse would never finish the Tour de France again. The winner of the previous edition, Bottecchia, said that he would retire from cycling, after the difficulties he faced in the 1926 Tour de France.\n\nThe Tour de France organisation did not like the outcome of the 1926 Tour de France, as 10 of the 17 stages had finished in bunch sprints. For the next year, the rules were changed, and the flat stages were run as team time trials.{{sfn|McGann|McGann|2006|pp=80\u201384}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{cite book|first=Jacques|last=Augendre|author-link=Jacques Augendre|url=http://netstorage.lequipe.fr/ASO/cyclisme/le-tour/2016/histoire/TDF16_GH_Interactif-PROD.pdf|title=Guide historique|trans-title=Historical guide|year=2016|language=French|access-date=27 October 2016|format=PDF|work=[[Tour de France]]|location=Paris|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817121602/http://netstorage.lequipe.fr/ASO/cyclisme/le-tour/2016/histoire/TDF16_GH_Interactif-PROD.pdf|archive-date=17 August 2016|url-status=live|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=McGann|first1=Bill|last2=McGann|first2=Carol|title=The Story of the Tour de France: 1903\u20131964|volume=1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jxq20JskqMUC|publisher=Dog Ear Publishing|location=Indianapolis, IN|year=2006|isbn=978-1-59858-180-5|ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Tour de France 1926|1926 Tour de France}}\n\n{{Cycling stage recaps|1926 Tour de France|1|9|10|17}}\n{{Tour de France}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tour De France}}\n[[Category:1926 Tour de France| ]]\n[[Category:1926 in road cycling]]\n[[Category:1926 in French sport|Tour de France]]\n[[Category:Tour de France by year|1926]]\n[[Category:June 1926 sports events|Tour de France]]\n[[Category:July 1926 sports events|Tour de France]]\n", "name_user": "BaldBoris", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInnovations:Changes from previous Tour \u2192 Innovations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1926_Tour_de_France"}
{"title_page": "List of Indonesian provinces by GRP per capita", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis article presents a '''list of [[provinces of Indonesia|Indonesian provinces]]''' sorted by their '''gross regional product nominal''' (GRP Nominal) per capita.\n\n== Methodology ==\nGRP Nominal is the regional or provincial counterpart of the national [[gross domestic product]], the most comprehensive measure of national economic activity. The [[Statistics Indonesia]] (''Badan Pusat Statistik'') derives GRP for a province as the sum of the GRP Nominal originating in all the industries in the province at current prices market.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238|title=Statistik Indonesia 2016|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|publisher=Badan Pusat Statistik|location=Jakarta|language=Indonesian|format=PDF|access-date=|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20161113201922/http://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238|archive-date=2016-11-13|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nList of Indonesian administrative divisions by GRP Nominal, with 14,140 IDR = US$1 term of Nominal while 4,325.87 IDR = US$1 term of PPP .<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-11-14 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20161113201922/http://www.bps.go.id/index.php/publikasi/4238 |archive-date=2016-11-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>. Note some provinces have little population and large oil, gas, or mining revenues, and therefore GRP Nominal does not reflect consumer demand.\n\n{{center|{{Indonesia provinces labelled map|thumb=y|caption=This clickable map shows province of Indonesia as of 25 October 2012. Click on a province name to go to its main article.}}}}\n\n==2019 data==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!Rank\n!Province\n!Region\n!GDP<br>(in billion [[Indonesian rupiah|Rp]])\n!GDP Nominal<br>(in billion [[US Dollar|$]])\n!GDP PPP<br>(in billion [[U